sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Controller as Spark Operator Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (metrics)
    participant Driver as Spark Driver Pod
    participant Executors as Spark Executor Pods
    participant ConnectSvc as SparkConnect Service<br/>15002/TCP gRPC

    Note over User, Executors: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. kubectl apply SparkApplication CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Admission Review (mutate + validate)<br/>HTTPS/443 → 9443, TLS self-signed
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR created/rejected

    K8sAPI->>Controller: 3. Watch event: SparkApplication created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. spark-submit → Create Driver Pod<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Pod created

    Driver->>K8sAPI: 5. Create Executor Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Driver: Executor Pods created
    Driver->>Executors: Execute Spark tasks

    Executors-->>Driver: Task results
    Driver-->>Controller: Driver pod completes (status watch)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update SparkApplication status<br/>(Running → Completed/Failed)

    Note over User, ConnectSvc: Flow 2: Spark Connect Server

    User->>ConnectSvc: 1. gRPC connection<br/>15002/TCP, No encryption, No auth
    ConnectSvc->>K8sAPI: 2. Create Executor Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    ConnectSvc->>Executors: 3. Distribute work<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP, No encryption

    Note over Controller, K8sAPI: Flow 3: Scheduled Spark Application

    Controller->>Controller: Cron trigger fires
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 1. Create SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Note right of Controller: 2. SparkApplication Controller<br/>takes over (see Flow 1)
